Sentencas: Dense electrolyte and porous cathode coatings by room-temperature operating aerosol deposition process are applied and optimized for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cell fabrication.
Titulo: Low temperature preparation and characterization of solid oxide fuel cells on FeCr-based alloy support by aerosol deposition

Sentencas: Porous metal support of FeCr-based alloy including (La, Sr)TiO3 diffusion barrier and (Ce, Gd)O2-delta-Ni anode were prepared using tape-casting process and co-fired in reducing atmosphere.
Titulo: Low temperature preparation and characterization of solid oxide fuel cells on FeCr-based alloy support by aerosol deposition

Sentencas: Dense (Zr, Y)O2-delta electrolyte and porous (La, Sr)(Co, Fe)O3-delta cathode were prepared using aerosol deposition on it.
Titulo: Low temperature preparation and characterization of solid oxide fuel cells on FeCr-based alloy support by aerosol deposition

Sentencas: The La0.2Sr0.8TiO3 diffusion barrier effectively suppressed the reaction between the FeCr-based alloy support and Ni in the anode during co-firing at 1300 degrees C. Room-temperature deposition of the electrolyte and cathode layers in low vacuum conditions effectively prevented metal support degradation and cathode decomposition.
Titulo: Low temperature preparation and characterization of solid oxide fuel cells on FeCr-based alloy support by aerosol deposition

Sentencas: Microstructural analysis of the anode, electrolyte, and cathode layers is presented.
Titulo: Low temperature preparation and characterization of solid oxide fuel cells on FeCr-based alloy support by aerosol deposition

Sentencas: An open circuit voltage of 1.08 V and maximum power density of 0.71 W/cm(2) were achieved at 750 degrees C. Copyright (C) 2014, Hydrogen Energy Publications, LLC.
